  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children with AIDS/TB-Treatment/Prevention. Since 2001 HOPE Cape Town has worked to reduce the AIDS/TB epidemic in the Western Cape region of South Africa through a multi-model approach involving Clinical, Social, Educational &amp; Nutritional direct care service to infected children &amp; their families.  25 Community Heath Workers provide counselling, facilitate access to healthcare, provide community support, assist with medical procedures, track patients, conduct home visits as 1st line of contact.</narrative>
  </description>
